   E-mail Alerts

   Delivered Fresh Daily

   E-mail alerts are breaking science news updates that are free
   to anyone that registers on our site.

   These alerts are customizable by topic and you may
   choose to receive these emails daily and/or weekly.

   You must login or register in order to utilize this feature.

   Divider

   1. Sign up on our website by clicking `register' the link
   at the upper right of any page.

   Register dialog box

   Divider

   2. Create your account for Science News by filling in the form fields. Click `Create account' and you will receive an email in your inbox with a confirmation code that completes your
   registration.

   Create account

   Divider

   3. Check your e-mail. You will receive a notification from us to click on a hyperlink to confirm your registration and proceed to completing your online profile.

   Email sample

   Divider

   4. After clicking the link from the email, you will be directed to complete your profile online at sciencenews.org. The highlighted boxes (shown in yellow below) indicate the fields that you
   need to change in order to receive your customized daily/weekly emails.

   While you're at this page, feel free to complete your profile to your liking. You can set an avatar image for when you post comments to articles, as well as update your pass-word and provide
   your SN subscriber number to access the online archives.

   Sample profile

   Divider

   That's it. You're done. Every night or every weekend, depending on the frequency of delivery that you choose, you will receive a fresh Science News email digest of the news that's happening in
   all areas of science.

